BSE - FRANCE (05)
*****************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
BSE - France (04) 980209230621
Date: Mon, 9 Feb 1998 12:21:12 EST
From: Angie Lee, Special Correspondent to ProMED-mail <Finchley@aol.com>
Source: News media

PARIS, Feb 9 - France on Monday reported a new case of BSE, the 33rd
incident in the country since 1990.
The affected cow, in a herd in the Savoie area near the French Alps, was
born in 1988 before a 1990 ban was imposed on cattle feed containing
ground-up animal parts, the Farm Ministry said in a statement. The 11 cows
in the herd were slaughtered over the weekend. An additional 67 cows were
also destroyed in the Haute-Savoie area because the diseased cow was born
and raised with that herd until December 1995.
--
