e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[A not uncommon marketing pattern is for cows culled from good herds to be
bought by marginal small-herd owners for breeding purposes and whatever
productivity remains. If this is the case here, as it appears, it might
explain how this cow survived so long. - Mod.MHJ
